items.title: Stellar 'pen work preserves lead in Yanks' win
items.summary: With the effects of Hurricane Irma forcing the series between the Yankees and Rays to Citi Field in Queens, the Yankees had a prime opportunity to capitalize on playing road games in their home city. They did just that, taking two of three from the Rays with a 3-2 win on Wednesday.

items.title: Papi rejoins Red Sox in multifaceted role
items.summary: Less than a year after his retirement, David Ortiz will be staying in the Red Sox's organization for the foreseeable future and hopefully for life.
items.content: Less than a year after his retirement, David Ortiz will be staying in the Red Sox's organization for the foreseeable future and hopefully for life.

items.title: Five series, one question remain for Cleveland
items.summary: When the Indians visited Chicago last week, there was no way to know if they were playing well or playing poorly. The tone in the clubhouse was quiet, calm and understated, like a team trying to get through June after going 5-5 in its last 10 games.

items.title: Giants receive award for work with youth
items.summary: hree organizations that speak to youth in a language they understand were recipients of the prestigious Robert Wood Johnson Foundation Sports Award on Wednesday morning, including the Giants Community Fund, The Moyer Foundation and PeacePlayers International.
